<p class="EnTeteTranscription">McKenzie, Charles. Journal of the Second, Third and Fourth Expeditions to the Missouri, 1805, 1806 with the Supplement to the Second Expedition. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0010</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p>N<sup>o</sup> 7</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The great Lodge was pulled to the ground &#8211; the adopted son threw off his fineries<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The women began to pack up <span class="DelHand-author">their alls</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The men ran for their horses &#8211; and each as soon as ready rode away<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Our party assembled upon an elevation behind the Camp where they expected and waited an attack<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Here the chiefs were busy animating the Young men &#8211; who were binding their bowes and brandis<span class="AddHand-author">h</span>ing their <span class="DelHand-author">batt</span> war axes anxious for battle<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The Chief who was on foot came to M<sup>r</sup> Chaboillez saying "my <span class="DelHand-author">Equal</span> <span class="AddHand-author">compeer</span> lend me your horse that I may go and speak to those dogs and learn whether they are for peace or for war<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>"  I then inquired of him if he wished to fight<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  No my son said he we do not wish to fight we have too many women and children <span class="AddHand-author">with us</span> &#8211; but if we are attacked we must defend ourselves <span class="DelHand-author">as</span> <span class="AddHand-author">li</span>ke men<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  When he had mounted he invited all those who were <span class="DelHand-author">men</span> <span class="AddHand-author">not afraid</span> to follow him &#8211; and all the men went and we formed upon the brow of a hill within <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Parler</span> of the Shayans who were <span class="DelHand-author">arranged</span> under arms &#8211; our chief addressed <span class="AddHand-author">them</span>.  "Shayan <span class="DelHand-author">'Said he'</span> I thought you had Known me before now<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  You invited me to Your Camp<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="DelHand-author">and</span> I came <span class="AddHand-author">mounted</span> with an open heart and brought peace with me<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  But you see me <span class="DelHand-author">go home</span> <span class="AddHand-author">return</span> on foot <span class="DelHand-author">and</span> <span class="AddHand-author">with</span> my heart full of anger<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I do not mean to praise myself, nor <span class="DelHand-author">will I</span> reproach You; I wish simply to Know whether you prefer war to peace.  Speak Shayans<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>"</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">"We know you well 'replied the Shayans'; <span class="DelHand-author">and</span> we did not invite you in anger<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The discord you see <span class="DelHand-author">has</span> originated with ourselves<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  When that discord is over we shall talk to you<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Go home in peace take Your time and fear not the Shayans<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>"  At this the two parties <span class="DelHand-author">turn</span> wheeled about; <span class="DelHand-author">and</span> <span class="AddHand-author">and</span> turned their backs upon one another<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="DelHand-author">and</span> <span class="DelHand-author"><span class="AddHand-author">and</span></span> Thus ended a serious quarrel &#8211; which gave us no small degree of <span class="DelHand-author">figh</span></p>
<p style="text-align:right;">fright</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[47]</span></p>

